SIMPLE: kiln
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Kiln
<hw>Kiln</hw> <pr>(k⟦icr⟧ln <it>or</it> k⟦icr⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[OE. <ets>kilne</ets>, <ets>kulne</ets>, AS. <ets>cyln</ets>,
<ets>cylen</ets>; akin to Icel. <ets>kylna</ets>; prob. from the same
source as <ets>coal</ets>. See <er>Coal</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
large stove or oven; a furnace of brick or stone, or a heated chamber,
for the purpose of hardening, burning, or drying anything; <as>as, a
<ex>kiln</ex> for baking or hardening earthen vessels; a <ex>kiln</ex>
for drying grain, meal, lumber, etc.; a <ex>kiln</ex> for calcining
limestone.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A furnace for burning bricks; a brickkiln.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kiln-dry</ent>⟦br⟧
